name: Wewe Gombel
description:
Wewe Gombel is a female supernatural being or ghost in Javanese mythology. Traditonally, the Wewe Gombel is represented as a woman with long, hanging breasts. 
It is said that she kidnaps children. This myth is taught to encourage children to be cautious and to stay at home at night. 
He didn't hurt them and once they were under his grip they weren't afraid of him.
She treats children lovingly like a grandmother, caring for them and protecting them until their parents repent, at which point she returns them.
